{{distinguish|archive.org}} {{selfref|For a guide to using '''archive.is''' within Wikipedia, see [[Wikipedia:Using archive.is]].}} {{short description|Online web archive}} {{lowercase title}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}} {{Infobox website | name = archive.is | logo = archive.is.jpg | screenshot = Archive.is-Screenshot.png | caption = Screenshot of archive.is | url = {{plain list| * {{URL|https://archive.today}} * {{URL|https://archive.is}} * {{URL|https://archive.li}} * {{URL|https://archive.fo}} * {{Onion URL|archivecaslytosk}} }} | alexa = {{DecreasePositive}} 2,897 ({{as of|2018|07|21|alt=July 2018}})<ref name="alexa">{{cite web |url=https://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/archive.is |title=Archive.is Site Info |website=Site Info |publisher=[[Alexa Internet]] |accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref> | commercial = No | type = [[Web archiving]] | language = [[Multilingualism|Multilingual]] | registration = No | launch date = {{start date and age|2012}} | current status = Online | revenue = | slogan = }}
'''archive.is''' (formerly '''archive.today''') is an [[archive site]] which stores snapshots of web pages.<ref name="cnet">{{cite web | url=https://www.ghacks.net/2015/04/22/create-publicly-available-web-page-archives-with-archive-is/ | title=Create publicly available web page archives with Archive.is | publisher=[[Ghacks]] | author = Martin Brinkmann | date=22 April 2015 | accessdate=13 June 2015 }}</ref> It retrieves one page at a time similar to [[WebCite]], smaller than 50&nbsp;MB each, but with [[Web 2.0]] sites (such as [[Google Maps]] and [[Twitter]]) included.
Archive.is uses [[headless browsing]] to record what embedded resources need to be captured to provide a high-quality [[Memento Project|memento]], and creates a [[Portable Network Graphics|PNG]] image to provide a static and non-interactive visualization of the representation.<ref>{{Cite journal |title = The impact of JavaScript on archivability |url = https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00799-015-0140-8 |journal = International Journal on Digital Libraries |publisher = Springer-Verlag Berlin Heidelberg |date = 2015-01-25 |df = dmy |volume = 17 |issue = 2 |pages = 95–117 |doi = 10.1007/s00799-015-0140-8 |first = Justin F. |last = Brunelle |first2 = Mat |last2 = Kelly |first3 = Michele C. |last3 = Weigle |first4 = Michael L. |last4 = Nelson}}</ref>
Unlike [[Web crawler|crawlers]] such as [[Wayback Machine]], archive.is only captures individual pages in response to explicit user requests, and so does not obey the [[robots exclusion standard]].<ref>{{cite web |first=Dan |last=Dascalescu |authorlink=Dan Dascalescu |url=https://wiki.dandascalescu.com/reviews/online_services/web_page_archiving |title=Web page archiving – Dan Dascalescu's Wiki (review) |publisher=Wiki.dandascalescu.com |date=18 February 2013 |accessdate=3 October 2013}}</ref> Because of this, website owners cannot unilaterally remove snapshots at will, making it a "permanent" archive.<ref name = "vice stealing">{{cite web |last=Koebler |first=Jason |url=https://motherboard.vice.com/read/dear-gamergate-please-stop-stealing-our-shit |title=Dear GamerGate: Please Stop Stealing Our Shit |date=29 October 2014 |work=Motherboard}}</ref>{{failed verification|date=November 2017}} <!--For example, [https://web.archive.org/web/*/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1295/is_9_65/ai_77811474 this] [[Archive.org]] link doesn't work; the error message "Page cannot be displayed due to robots.txt." is displayed, but [https://archive.is/20120717223848/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1295/is_9_65/ai_77811474 this] Archive.is archive of the same URL does still work. -- Why commented out: Better example would be where the same error came up at archive.org, and the original content was gone, as in this example but archive.is had *directly* archived the content, rather than indirectly, as in this case. Good enough?-->
Since July 2013, archive.is supports the [[Memento Project]] [[application programming interface]] (API).<ref name=WSRG>{{cite web|url=https://ws-dl.blogspot.nl/2013/07/2013-07-09-archiveis-supports-memento.html |title=Archive.is Supports Memento |publisher=Web Science and Digital Libraries Research Group at [[Old Dominion University]] |work=Research and Teaching Updates |date=9 July 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130727194715/https://ws-dl.blogspot.de/2013/07/2013-07-09-archiveis-supports-memento.html |archivedate=27 July 2013 |deadurl=no |accessdate=17 September 2013 |first=Michael L. |last=Nelson |df=dmy }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://mementoweb.org/depot/native/archiveis/|title=archive.is|website=Memento Protocol Information|publisher=Memento Development Group|accessdate=17 September 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130915191950/https://mementoweb.org/depot/native/archiveis/|archivedate=15 September 2013}}</ref>
