== Features == Archive.is records only text and images, excluding video and other [[static web page|non-static]] content. It keeps track of the history of snapshots saved, returning to the user a request for confirmation before adding a new snapshot of an already saved Internet address.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://archive.is/https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/6062608?hl=en | title = Example snapshot history on archive.is}}{{cbignore}}</ref>
At November 2018, Archive.is codifies snapshots with an [[alphanumeric]] [[case-sensitive]] code of five elements. Hence, any element may have one of 42 possible values, between: # ten [[Numerical digit|digits]], from 0 to 9. # 32 letters, 16 of the [[English alphabet]], whose number is doubled by 16 capital letter. The global amount of possible combinations is given by the [[conditional probability#statistical independence|conditional probability]] theorem, as follows: <math>42^5 = 130.691</math> milions of identifiers. The number of available [[URL#syntax|URI]]s can be additionally extended with the use of [[plus and minus signs|plus and minus]], [[colon (punctuation)|colon]], [[underscore]] or [[slash (punctuation)|slash]] signs.
Web pages cannot be [[Redundancy (engineering)|duplicated]] from ''<nowiki>http://archive.is</nowiki>'' to ''<nowiki>http://www.archive.org</nowiki>'' as [[Remote backup service|second-level backup]]. The reverse - from ''<nowiki>www.archive.org</nowiki>'' to ''<nowiki>archive.is</nowiki>'' - is possible,<ref name="Wayback Mach to archive.is">{{cite web | url = Http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Christ | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130517180220/Http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Christ | dead-url = yes | archive-date = 2013-05-17 | title = Example: Page saved from Web Archive to Archive.is}}</ref> but the copy usually takes more time than a direct capture. Some web sites can't be saved by either [[Internet Archive]] or archive.is due to their [[robots.txt]] file.
The research toolbar enables advanced keywords operators, using {{code|*}} as the [[Wildcard character#Computing|wildcard character]]. A couple of [[quotation mark]]s address the search to an exact sequence of keywords present in the title or in the body of the webpage, whereas the ''insite'' operator restricts it to a specific Internet domain<ref>For example, the string <nowiki>insite: https://en.wikipedia.org "World Cup"</nowiki> returns the [http://archive.fo/search/?q=insite%3A+http%3Aen.wikipedia.org+"World+Cup"/ related snapshots]</ref>.
Once a web page is archived, it cannot be deleted directly by any Internet<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.google. com/amp/s/blog.archive.is/post/41395737942/how-can-i-delete-an-archived-page/amp | title = Some Frequently Asked Question | website = archive.is blog | language = en | access-date = Nov 12, 2018 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130926093655/https://blog.archive.is/post/41395737942/how-can-i-delete-an-archived-page | archive-date = Sep 26, 2013 | deadurl = no}}</ref>.
