'''Java backporting tools''' are programs (usually written in [[Java (programming language)|Java]]) that convert Java classes [[Java bytecode|bytecodes]] from one version of the [[Java (software platform)|Java Platform]] to an older one (for example Java 5.0 backported to 1.4).
