{{infobox book | name = The Guerilla Filmmakers Handbook | title_orig = | translator = | image = TheGuerillaFilmmakersHandbook.jpg | caption = | author = [[Chris Jones (filmmaker)|Chris Jones]] and Genevieve Jolliffe | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United Kingdom | language = English | series = | genre = [[Non-fiction]] | publisher = Continuum International Publishing Group Ltd. | release_date = 2006 (third edition) | english_release_date = | media_type = [[Paperback]] | pages = 768 | isbn = 0-8264-7988-X | oclc= 67374318 | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''The Guerilla Filmmakers Handbook''''' is a bestselling<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/082647988X/ |title=Amazon.com synopsis |accessdate=2006-12-20 |work=Amazon.com }}</ref> [[textbook]] on [[Low-budget film|low-budget]] and [[independent film]] production written by [[Chris Jones (filmmaker)|Chris Jones]] and Genevieve Jolliffe. Currently in its third edition, it consists primarily of interviews with filmmakers and case studies in [[filmmaking]]. The Handbook has become widely respected in the UK as a comprehensive filmmaking guide.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.britfilms.com/resources/publications/ |title=Essential publications |accessdate=2006-12-20 |work=Britfilms.com }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/dna/filmnetwork/filmmakersguidereading |title=Recommended Reading |accessdate=2006-12-20 |work=BBC Film Network}}</ref>
Jones and Jolliffe have also written three further books on film making. Chris Jones wrote The Guerilla Film Makers Movie Blueprint. Jones and Jolliffe also co-authored the US Guerilla Film Makers Handbook (aka Hollywood Handbook in the UK). Genevieve Jolliffe and Andrew Zinnes also wrote The Documentary Film Makers Handbook. Most recently the trio published the Guerilla Film Makers Pocketbook.
Jones and Jolliffe, the authors have made three low-budget movies: ''The Runner'' (1992), ''[[White Angel (1994 film)|White Angel]]'' (1993) and ''Urban Ghost Story'' (1998). They also run courses in filmmaking through their production company, Living Spirit Pictures. Jolliffe now resides in Los Angeles, Jones now in Ealing, London, where their offices are based ([[Ealing Studios]]). Chris Jones recently directed an Oscars shortlisted short film, ''[[Gone Fishing (2008 film)|Gone Fishing]]'', which won awards at over 40 international film festivals.
Film makers who cite the Guerilla Film Makers Handbook and its follow up books as influential to them include Simon Cox, the Writer/Director of ''Kaleidoscope Man'' and [[Allin Kempthorne]], the Writer/Director of ''[[The Vampires of Bloody Island]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guerillafilm.com/movie-blueprint/reader-feedback/ |title=Blueprint Book Feedback}}</ref>
